<TITLE> Dipjol gets bail, faces no bar to release </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)The High Court granted bail for six months to actor and alleged crime kingpin Monwar Hossain Dipjol in an illegal assets case on Monday, clearing way for his release from jail, said his lawyer. With his securing the bail from the bench of justices AM Abdur Rahman and SM Emdadul Haq, Dipjol now has no legal bar to stepping out of the prison, his lawyer Munsurul Haq Chowdhury told bdnews24.com. Of the six cases he faces, the High Court overturned on Sunday convictions in two arms cases totalling 24 years, while he is on bail in three other cases, the lawyer said. The Special Judge's Court, Dhaka on Nov. 13 last year sentenced him to 13 years in prison in the illegal wealth accumulation case. The former BNP ward commissioner was arrested in Adabar in the capital on Dec. 9 last year
